name: Tornado
summary: Severe weather impacted multiple regions on Saturday and Sunday. In Louisville, Kentucky, a tornado watch was in effect, while a tornado struck Texas, resulting in confirmed fatalities in Cook County. Iowa was also hit hard, with multiple tornadoes causing at least five deaths and 35 injuries in Greenfield. The National Weather Service issued an event summary for May 21, 2024, detailing tornadoes, winds, and flash flooding. Eyewitness accounts and footage from a Tesla dashcam captured the intensity of the Texas tornado. Search and rescue operations are ongoing in Iowa after the deadly tornado struck, and a tornado warning was issued for East Tennessee due to storms.

name: George Floyd
summary: In the aftermath of George Floyd's murder four years ago, the nation faced a critical examination of policing practices. Despite the widespread protests and calls for reform, progress has been slow or reversed, as highlighted in reports by NBC News, Reuters, and CBS News. The "No Justice, No Streets" movement continues to stand in protest at George Floyd Square, a symbol of the ongoing struggle for justice. Despite some "steady but slow" advancements against racism, as acknowledged by USA Today, many of Minnesota's racial gaps remain stark, according to the Minnesota Reformer. The Los Angeles Times warns of a backlash against efforts to address systemic racism. Amidst these challenges, a big-screen biopic of George Floyd is in production, with his daughter serving as an executive producer.
